We've got a burgeoning private space industry with companies like Xcor Aerospace, Armadillo Aerospace, Scaled Composites(the first privately funded supersonic manned rocket launch), and Orbital Sciences racing to make money on the environment space provides. <br>
If you drew a parallel between the space and computer industries, we're basically just starting to drive down the cost of mainframes. There's the idea of the PC (or reusable launch vehicle) being cheap and efficient. But until the industry truly gets privatized and out of government hands, it won't be cheap. <br>
<br>
